{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778698686,"nonce":"RcU8XWKX+3csBBIEn33ft/6twjk=","message":"**Refinement: helper-level trim + shared y-axes (4 commits).**\n\nAfter the initial fix landed, two follow-ups surfaced from re-rendered figures:\n\n1. **Choppy NaN edges after `align_trials`.** Added `trim_to_full_support(aligned, min_coverage=1.0)` to `rlrmp.analysis.trial_alignment`. Default returns the strict full-support window (every (replicate, trial) sample contributes). Wired into `pooled_trial_mean_with_band` and `replicate_mean_curves` as `trim=True` default; both surface the trim slice so callers can clip their companion time axis. Pass `trim=False` only when downstream code needs identical step axes across multiple invocations (e.g. cross-cell pairwise RMSE; the lit-replication and anti-anticipation cross-cell-RMSE paths use this).\n\n2. **Per-cell subplots on independent y-axes.** Added `rlrmp.viz.profile_comparison_grid` — a thin `make_subplots` wrapper that defaults `shared_yaxes='all'`. The three analysis scripts (`analyse_pregomatrix.py`, `analyse_lit_replication_6cell.py`, `analyse_anti_anticipation_6cell_variance.py`) now build the velocity / hold-drift grids via this helper, so no per-script `shared_yaxes` knob is needed. The policy is codified in CLAUDE.md under the new \"Plotting Conventions\" section.\n\n**Within-cell vel-RMSE values changed** because they were computed on aligned profiles with NaN edges before; with trim they're now on the strict full-support window. The conclusions (winner cells) are unchanged. Headline magnitude shifts on 3702f54: `post_go_pl__pos10` from 0.1426 → 0.1002; `full_trial_pl__pos10` from 0.1841 → 0.1491; etc.\n\n**Commits (on feature/go-cue-alignment-fix):**\n- `17fb3ff` Add trim_to_full_support helper and wire into aggregators\n- `892eb1b` Add profile_comparison_grid with shared y-axes; wire trim through analysis scripts\n- `71305ea` Codify shared-y-axis and trim conventions for profile figures\n- `76bedd7` Re-render profile figures with trim + shared y-axes; record in specs\n\nNo prior Codex work on shared y-axes was found (grepped commit history, branch list, and `~/.codex/sessions/2026/05/`).","files":null}]}